name: WebBackForwardList
desc: A WebBackForwardList object maintains a list of visited pages used to go back and forward to the most recent page. A WebBackForwardList object maintains only the list dataâ€”it does not perform actual page loads (in other words, it does not make any client requests). If you need to perform a page load, see the load(_:) method in WebFrame to find out how to do this.

items.name: func add(WebHistoryItem!)
items.desc: Inserts an item into the back-forward list, immediately after the current item.

items.name: func goBack()
items.desc: Moves backward one item in the back-forward list.

items.name: func goForward()
items.desc: Moves forward one item in the back-forward list.

items.name: func go(to: WebHistoryItem!)
items.desc: Makes the specified item in the back-forward list the current item.

items.name: var backItem: WebHistoryItem!
items.desc: The item that precedes the current item in the back-forward list.

items.name: var backListCount: Int32
items.desc: The number of items that precede the current item in the back-forward list.

items.name: func back(withLimit: Int32) -> [Any]!
items.desc: Returns the items that precede the current item in the back-forward list, up to the specified number of items.

items.name: func contains(WebHistoryItem!) -> Bool
items.desc: Returns a Boolean value indicating whether the back-forward list contains the specified item.

items.name: var currentItem: WebHistoryItem!
items.desc: The current item in the back-forward list.

items.name: func item(at: Int32) -> WebHistoryItem!
items.desc: Returns the item at the specified index in the back-forward list.

items.name: var forwardItem: WebHistoryItem!
items.desc: The item that follows the current item in the back-forward list.

items.name: var forwardListCount: Int32
items.desc: The number of items that follow the current item in the back-forward list.

items.name: func forwardList(withLimit: Int32) -> [Any]!
items.desc: Returns the items that follow the current item in the back-forward list, up to the specified number of items.

items.name: func pageCacheSize() -> Int
items.desc: Returns the maximum number of pages that the receiver can cache.

items.name: func setPageCacheSize(Int)
items.desc: Sets the maximum number of pages the receiver can cache.

items.name: var capacity: Int32
items.desc: The maximum number of items that the back-forward list can contain.
